  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="FR">OCHA Secondment Humanitarian Affairs Officer</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="FR">South Sudan is facing a protracted humanitarian crisis dominated by internal insecurity, food security, influx of refugees, IDPs and returnees. Jonglei State has seen serious inter- as well as intra-communal fighting in 2011/2012 and 2013. This lead OCHA in early 2012 to set up a temporary &#x91;Advanced Coordination Hub&#x92; in Pibor County. With improved access, multiple and simultaneous interventions are taking place in Jonglei State. OCHA has requested additional external capacities to provide quality coordination to this complex emergency response. SDC seconds OCHA a humanitarian affairs officer to support the humanitarian response to displacements from Jonglei State.</narrative>
  </description>
